Instruction:
 1. sh gen.sh / sh gen.sh.test  [modify time for cron job first]
    output:
      job_make_ctest.scr
      crontab.txt
 2. crontab  `pwd`/crontab.txt
 3. crontab -l    [check job]


Attention:
- a deficiency in the design:
  - I have a hard coded directory name:
    base=/glade/scratch/$USER/br_autotest/br_$mydate
    - br: branch
    - mydate: today's date in format, for example, 2022-11-18
  - You can change the base name throughout the repository by 
    - sed -i 's#br_autotest#YYYY#g' file-name-one-by-one

Basic terminal command:
- crontab -l  :  list installed crontab
- crontab -e  :  installing new crontab

const files
- step1.sh [ checkout_ecbuild.sh : check out bundle, ecbuild        ]
- step2.sh [ make_ctest.sh :  make -j 16; tag CMakelists.txt; ctest ]
- step3.sh [ use MPASWorkflow to submit cycle jobs                  ]
- step4.sh [ graphics plot :  first check cycle finish correctly    ]
- gen.sh   [ gen crontab.txt: job_make_ctest.scr                    ]

assist files (generated by gen.sh)
- gen.sh
  - gen crontab.txt
  - job_make_ctest.scr 
    - to submit a job for make and ctest

- crontab.txt
  - step1.sh (ecbuild)
  - step2.sh (make; ctest)
  - step3.sh (120-km cycle)
  - step4.sh (graphics)
